The paper deals with graph isomorphism and related combinatorial and algebraic graph properties, which are typical topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of linear programming and complexity analysis also suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), and machine learning (cs.LG).
